==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Publicity pamphlet
<hw>Publicity pamphlet</hw>. <def>A pamphlet which, in some States of
the United States having the initiative or referendum, is mailed to the
voters to inform them as to the nature of a measure submitted by the
initiative or referendum. The pamphlet contains a copy of the proposed
law and arguments for and against it by those favoring and opposing it,
respectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

